			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>Parse Table Composition: Separate Compilation and Binary Extensibility of Grammars</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/MartinBravenboer.html">Martin Bravenboer</a>, <a href="../profile/EelcoVisser.html">Eelco Visser</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_6">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_6</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagM">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It addresses modularity and separate compilation for grammars via parse-table composition.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It is fundamentally about compilation technology for parsing (constructing and composing parse tables).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagL">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> The approach enables reuse of independently developed grammar components without recompiling the whole parser.
</li></ul></li></ul>
